<TITLE> Elevated expressway could be first PPP venture </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 18 (bdnews24.com)International pre-qualification tenders will be invited for Bangladesh's first elevated expressway on Thursday, communications ministry officials say. Officials of the Bangladesh Bridge Authority, under the communications ministry, said on Wednesday it will be the first online tender of the country. The Tk 17,000 crore ($2.5 billion) project could also be the first under the government's public-private partnership initiative. Public relations officer Bharat Chandra Mandol told bdnews24.com that the BBA will publish details of the tender on dailies and on its own website. "All conditions for floating the tender for the expressway have been laid down by the bridge authority. Participants will not be required to pay for tender schedules," Mondal said. They can collect tender schedules free of cost from the bridge authority office and from the website which is www.bba.gov.bd, he said Executive engineer Liaquat Ali said: "The government will select the prequalification tenders for investment in the project." He said the deadline for submission of tender schedules would be Jan 20, 2010. b
